&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you a dedicated and motivated personal trainer looking to make a significant impact on individuals&#39; lives? We are actively seeking exceptional trainers to join our team and deliver personalized fitness experiences in the comfort of our clients&#39; homes. Join us and be a part of a dynamic community that values your expertise, provides flexibility, and supports your professional growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you a dedicated and motivated personal trainer looking to make a significant impact on individuals&#39; lives? We are actively seeking exceptional group fitness trainers to join our team and deliver personalized fitness experiences to our clients. Join us and be a part of a dynamic community that values your expertise, provides flexibility, and supports your professional growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take pride in our commitment to building an environment that embraces individuals from different genders, backgrounds, and ethnicities. Our organization values diversity and encourages candidates of all gender identities, backgrounds, and ethnicities to apply. We believe in creating an inclusive space where every individual feels welcome, respected, and valued. Join us in our mission to foster a workplace that celebrates the unique perspectives and experiences of our diverse team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JOB RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TEACH “Circuit Training” to 2 to 3 participants in an office gym located in Randolph, MA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Usually there will be 8 to 10 exercises in the circuit, although this number can vary based on time available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To get the most from the circuit training for those participating, it is best to perform a full-body workout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have access to weights, machines and the use of body weight to develop a full circuit training workout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must have a written workout plan before teaching the class as there may be both beginners and intermediate participants in the class.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate must have a personal training certificate such as NASM, ISSA, etc. that is current.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPR/AED certificate must be current.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background check required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to instruct the class two times a week starting at 4:30 pm to 5:30 pm. The days can be Mon &amp;amp; Wed or Tues &amp;amp; Thurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have reliable transportation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instructor must always be on time because those attending the circuit training will be getting off work in the building at 4:30 PM and ready to start the circuit training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with Mindbody application but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We take pride in our commitment to building an environment that embraces individuals from different genders, backgrounds, and ethnicities. Our organization values diversity and encourages candidates of all gender identities, backgrounds, and ethnicities to apply. We believe in creating an inclusive space where every individual feels welcome, respected, and valued. Join us in our mission to foster a workplace that celebrates the unique perspectives and experiences of our diverse team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

